Text: Aaaaaagh!!!
Eep...! Ulp...

Clack... Clack... The sound of footsteps ring outâ€”
A black silhouette emerges from the darkness.
We are the Shadow Garden...
H-Help...
We are the Shadow Garden...
Ah, d-don't!!!
We are the Shadow Garden...
We are...
(Summer's almost here.)

(It's that time of day when Skel and Po corner me in
the cafeteria, their faces burning with curiosity.)
So, how'd it go with Princess Alexia?
Yeah, yeah!
I swear, we parted ways and that's it.
(And I almost got killed in the process.)
No smooching? Not even a little peck?
Mmmm...!
Nope.
Ugh, what a letdown...

Alright, I got it. I know a really good place that'll
cheer ya up.
A-A really good place?!
Po breathes heavily through his nose.

Not "that" type of place. I mean Mitsugoshi, the
place everyone's been talkin' about lately.

Word is they sell all kindsa stuff nobody's ever seen
or heard of before, and they've even got this candy
called "chocolate" that's supposed to be hella tasty.
Candy? I like the sound of that.
You dumbass! It's not for you to eat.

It's a present for the ladies. Give a girl somethin'
sweet, and she'll be yours, just like that.
O-Oh, I got it. Gee, Skel, you're the smartest.
You know it!
Let's get movin', Cid!
Yeah, c'mon, Cid!
Skel and Po's eyes gleam eagerly.
Okay, fine. Let's go.
I let out a resigned sigh as I speak.

(Well, I do have to admit I'm a little interested in
seeing the "chocolate" of this world.)

Skel brought the group to one of the main streets of
the royal capital.

(The evening thoroughfare is full of people, and at
all the nearby shops business is booming. But the
most crowded shop by a large margin is the much-
rumored Mitsugoshi.)

(The architecture is modern and fancy, like something
out of my past life.)

(And everyone in line is an upper-cruster...
Man, talk about being out-of-place.)

(The line winds from the entrance like a snake,
and at the very end is a lady in uniform holding a
placard.)
The current wait is 80 minutes.
You heard her.

Wh-What should we do? We'd probably make it home
before curfew, but... There's all that talk of a
slasher roaming the streets at night lately...
A slasher?

Po, are you stupid or what? We got three dark knights
right here. Any sicko that comes at us'll get sent
packin'.
Y-Yeah, I guess so.
Hey, what's this slasher talk?

They say a killer has been stalking the capital after
sundown lately. And they must be pretty skilled,
since apparently even the Knight Order has lost
people now...
Dang, no more night time strolls for me.
(A slasher cutscene? Sign me up.)
Let's get in line, fast! We're gonna miss curfew.
(At Skel's urging, we join the end of the line.)

H-H-Hello, miss. Y-You're pretty. Wh-What're your
hobbies?

(Skel wastes no time chatting up the lady with the
placard, but she brushes him off with the smile of
a battle-hardened veteran.)

(She's a real beauty with fine, calm features
complemented with dark brown hair and eyes.)

(Her uniform is a simple, navy blue mini one-piece
dress with the company logo on it. The overall look
reminds me of a flight attendant from somewhere
back in my past life.)
Pardon me, sir, but do you have a moment?

Yes, it won't take long. I was hoping you would take
part in a survey.

(A survey. You don't see a lot of those
in this world.)
Sure, I don't mind, I guess...
I-I-I'LL DO IT!
M-Me, too!
(Skel and Po offer themselves up eagerly.)
Just one of you will do. Right this way, sir.
Uh, okay.
Wha?!

(The lady links her arm through mine and then leads
me away from the long line into the store.)

(I glance back right before going inside to see Skel
and Po watching me with forlorn eyes.)

(I follow the lady inside the shop, which proves to
be quite fancy.)
Wow.

(The interior isnâ€™t outwardly garish, but I can tell
every last detail of decor has been carefully selected,
and it gives off a chill vibe.)

(There is definitely something modern about how it
conveys an appreciated aesthetic in a way even
untrained eyes can understand.)

(It's just like a department store in my old life.
And it's the first time I've seen things like
chocolate and coffee in this world, so I'm
definitely puzzled.)

(The whole place is filled with stuff even I know
will surely sell.)

(Pretty amazing either way you look at it.
This company is gonna be top dog in
the near future. Iâ€™m sure of it.)
So...what was this about a survey?
Hm?
Wow.

(I follow the silent lady and before long a set of
huge, gleaming doors decorated with chic
engravings appears before me.)
(The doors open slowly...)
